<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12029d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12029d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12029d"> 29(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> white robe / gilt leather belt houppe de laine &amp; 2 back bands / like mitre / (archdruid)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les chefs des Druides portoient une robe blanche, ceinte d&apos;une bande de cuir dor&eacute;, un rochet &amp; un bonnet blanc tout simple; &amp; leur souverain Pontife &eacute;toit distingu&eacute; par une houppe de laine avec deux bandes d&apos;&eacute;toffe, qui pendoient derri&egrave;re comme aux m&icirc;tres des &Eacute;v&ecirc;ques. <br><font color="green">[The chief Druids wore a white robe with a gilt leather belt, a surplice and a very simple white cap; and their sovereign high priest was distinguished by a woollen tassel with two strips of cloth, which hung at the back like the strips at the back of bishops&apos; mitres.]</font> <small> M. Sabbathier, <a name="MSAD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MSAD"><cite title="source">Dictionnaire pour l'intelligence des auteurs classiques, Grecs et Latins</cite></a> (1773) 494</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12012j" href="c12all.htm#c12012j">VI.C.12:012(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
